Wrapper Classes¶

Address¶

class SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Address : public ExpandableObjectConverter, public SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.IDatabaseWrapper¶

This class represents an address. An address in the case of Survey Manager does not have a state associated with it.

All addresses are assumed to be in the state of Texas.

This class implements the IDatabaseWrapper interface to facilitate easier database operations.

Public Functions

DatabaseError Insert ()¶

Defines the behaviour for inserting the object’s data into the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Update ()¶

Defines the behaviour for updating the object’s data in the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Delete ()¶

Defines the behaviour for deleting the object from the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

Properties

string Street { get; set; } = string.Empty¶

The street component of the address.

string City { get; set; } = string.Empty¶

The city component of the address.

string ZipCode { get; set; } = string.Empty¶

The zip-code component of the address.

bool IsEmpty { get; set; }¶

Get a value indicating if this address is considered to be empty.

Returns true if the street, city, or zip-code are empty strings.

CFile¶

class SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.CFile : public SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.IDatabaseWrapper¶

This class represents files. The main method of note in this class is ReadAllBytes(string). This method will actually populate this file object with the data in the actual file on disk.

This class implements the IDatabaseWrapper interface to facilitate easier database operations.

Public Functions

bool ReadAllBytes (string path)¶

Reads all of the bytes of the file in path into the Contents property.

Param path

The path to the file to read from.

Return

True if the file was read successfully; False otherwise.

string GetTempFile ()¶

Get a file path to this CFile object. The temporary file is deleted after the program is closed.

Return

The path to the temporary file.

override string ToString ()¶

Override for object.ToString() that returns a readable version of this CFile.

Return

FileName.Extension

DatabaseError Insert ()¶

Defines the behaviour for inserting the object’s data into the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Update ()¶

Defines the behaviour for updating the object’s data in the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Delete ()¶

Defines the behaviour for deleting the object from the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

Properties

string FileName { get; set; } = ""¶

The file name, without an extension, for this file.

string Description { get; set; } = ""¶

A brief description for this file explaining what it is.

FileExtension Extension { get; set; } = FileExtension.NONE¶

The extension of this file. This is limited to the options in FileExtension.

string FullFileName { get; set; }¶

The full file name including its extension.

string TempPath { get; set; }¶

A temporary path on disk to this file object.

byte[] Contents { get; set; }¶

The raw byte array representing the file’s contents.

Encoding FileEncoding { get; set; } = Encoding.Default¶

Get the encoding for this file.

string FileSize { get; set; }¶

The size of the file as a formatted string. The string will be formatted as {size} {unit}, i.e. 5 MB for 5 megabytes.

bool IsValidFile { get; set; }¶

Get a value indicating if this is a valid file and thus ready to be saved to the database.

A valid file is one whose contents are not null or empty and has a file name and extension.

Bitmap DisplayIcon { get; set; }¶

Get the icon to display for this file based on its Extension property.

Client¶

class SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Client : public ExpandableObjectConverter, public SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.IDatabaseWrapper¶

This class represents a Client object. A client is associated with a SurveyJob.Survey.

This class implements the IDatabaseWrapper interface to facilitate easier database operations.

Public Functions

void SetAddress ()¶

Set the ClientAddress object from the database based on the id in AddressID. Runs on a seperate thread.

DatabaseError Insert ()¶

Defines the behaviour for inserting the object’s data into the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Update ()¶

Defines the behaviour for updating the object’s data in the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Delete ()¶

Defines the behaviour for deleting the object from the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

Properties

string Name { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The full name of the client.

string PhoneNumber { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The phone number of the client.

string Email { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The email address of the client.

string FaxNumber { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The fax number, if any, of the client.

int AddressID { get; set; }¶

The id for this client’s address in the database.

Address ClientAddress { get; set; } = new Address()¶

The Address for this client object.

bool IsValidClient { get; set; }¶

Get a value indicating if the client is valid. A valid client is one whose name and phone number is not “N/A” and whose address is not empty.

IDatabaseWrapper¶

interface SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.IDatabaseWrapper¶

All classes that are considered to be database wrappers should implement this interface.

Subclassed by SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Address, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.CFile, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Client, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.County, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Realtor, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.SurveyJob.Billing, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.SurveyJob.BillingItem, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.SurveyJob.LineItem, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.SurveyJob.Rate, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.SurveyJob.Survey, SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.TitleCompany

Defines the behaviour for deleting the object from the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

The id (primary key) of the database record.

Realtor¶

class SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.Realtor : public ExpandableObjectConverter, public SurveyManager.backend.wrappers.IDatabaseWrapper¶

This class represents a Realtor object. A realtor is associated with a SurveyJob.Survey.

This class implements the IDatabaseWrapper interface to facilitate easier database operations.

Public Functions

DatabaseError Insert ()¶

Defines the behaviour for inserting the object’s data into the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Update ()¶

Defines the behaviour for updating the object’s data in the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Delete ()¶

Defines the behaviour for deleting the object from the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

Properties

string Name { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The full name of the realtor.

string CompanyName { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The company name where the realtor works.

string Email { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The email address for the realtor.

string PhoneNumber { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The phone number for the realtor.

string FaxNumber { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The fax number, if any, for the realtor.

bool IsValidRealtor { get; set; }¶

Get a value representing whether this Realtor is valid or not.

A valid Realtor is one whose name, email, and company name is not equal to “N/A” and not an empty string.

This class implements the IDatabaseWrapper interface to facilitate easier database operations.

Defines the behaviour for inserting the object’s data into the database.

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

DatabaseError Delete ()¶

Return

A DatabaseError enum representing the result of the method.

Properties

string Name { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The full name of the title company.

string AssociateName { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The full name of the associate (point of contact) for the title company.

string AssociateEmail { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The email address for the associated (point of contact) for the title company.

string OfficeNumber { get; set; } = "N/A"¶

The phone number for the title company’s office.

bool IsValidCompany { get; set; }¶

Get a value indiciating if this is a valid TitleCompany.
